Feature: Legilimens

    Allows the caster to delve into the mind of the victim, allowing the caster
    to see the memories, thoughts, and emotions of the victim.

    Pronunciation:
        /lɛˈdʒɪlɨmɛnz/ le-JIL-i-menz
    Seen/mentioned:
        Used by Snape on Harry during Occlumency lessons in Order of the
        Phoenix and by Dumbledore on Kreacher. Also used nonverbally by Snape
        on Harry in Half-Blood Prince to allow him to see where Harry had
        learned the Sectumsempra spell. Used by Lord Voldemort multiple times
        to see Harry's thoughts.
    Suggested etymology: - 
    Notes:
        See also Legilimency for more information.